
[1]inquisitive

   INQUIS'ITIVE, a. s as z. Apt to ask questions; addicted to inquiry;
   inclined to seek information by questions; followed by about or after.
   He was very inquisitive about or after news. Children are usually
   inquisitive.

   1. Inclined to seek knowledge by discussion, investigation or
   observation; given to research. He possesses an inquisitive mind or
   disposition. We live in an inquisitive age.

   INQUIS'ITIVE, n. A person who is inquisitive; one curious in research.
     __________________________________________________________________

